dct_title_s: A plan of the city of New York from an actual survey [copy 2]
dct_description_sm: Covers lower Manhattan south of the current location of the Brooklyn Bridge. Shows wards, streets, and public buildings. "C.2."--Upper right corner. Facsimile of the original map published by William Bradford in 1728. Possibly accompanies: The Bradford map : the city of New York at the time of the granting of the Montgomery charter: a description thereof / compiled by William Loring Andrews. New York : De Vinne Press, 1893.
